byline.contributor: Tim Arango contributed reporting from Istanbul.
byline.original: By OMAR AL-JAWOSHY and FALIH HASSAN

abstract: Protesters breach walls of Green zone in Baghdad, marking second time in three weeks demonstrators have forced their way into secure government zone; incident provides further evidence of rising Iraqi discontent with leadership.
lead_paragraph: A short-lived but telling show of unrest as security forces fire tear gas to remove demonstrators who had stormed the prime minister’s office.

headline.main: Iraqi Protesters Clash With Troops in Baghdad’s Green Zone
headline.print_headline: Baghdad Protesters Clash With Troops in Green Zone
